---
// Search results shell — EMPTY containers the ported client JS populates at
// runtime. The JS injects a.ritem#roptN[role=option] rows and the .nr
// no-results catalog into #results, and writes live status text into #q-status.
// We emit ONLY the shells, byte-for-byte from docs/index.html — no props, no
// interactivity here. Selectors/attributes are part of the DOM contract that
// the ported JS (and ARIA combobox wiring on #q) depends on; do NOT change them.
---

<div class="results" id="results" role="listbox" aria-label="Search results"></div>
<div id="q-status" class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
